Pre-Game Insights: Devin Booker and the Phoenix Suns host the Atlanta Hawks in a non-conference matchup.
The Suns are 10-8 in home games and have a 5-9 record in games decided by 10 points or more.
The Hawks have gone 9-11 away from home and are the top team in the Eastern Conference with 55.0 points per game in the paint, led by Jalen Johnson averaging 12.2.
The Suns score 111.8 points per game, 8.0 fewer points than the 119.8 the Hawks allow.
The Hawks are shooting 46.4% from the field, which equals what the Suns' opponents have shot this season.
Booker is averaging 24.6 points and 6.8 assists for the Suns.
Trae Young is scoring 22.6 points per game with 3.5 rebounds and 12.2 assists for the Hawks.

In their last 10 games, the Suns are 2-8, averaging 106.3 points, 41.3 rebounds, 27.3 assists, 7.3 steals, and 5.8 blocks per game while shooting 45.9% from the field. Their opponents have averaged 113.4 points per game.

In their last 10 games, the Hawks are 5-5, averaging 120.3 points, 43.3 rebounds, 30.5 assists, 11.5 steals, and 5.6 blocks per game while shooting 47.6% from the field. Their opponents have averaged 122.5 points.
Others: Suns' player Royce O'Neale is out due to an ankle injury.

Hawks' players Kobe Bufkin is out for the season with a shoulder injury, Larry Nance Jr. is out with a hand injury, Jalen Johnson is day-to-day with a shoulder injury, and Cody Zeller is day-to-day due to personal reasons.
